<!-- AESTHETICS -->

<section id="aesthetics" class="section container">

<h1>Aesthetics & Design</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">
<img src="images/aesthetic.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">
</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Caribbean aesthetics reflect the cultural fusion of African heritage,
indigenous traditions, and modern diasporic identity. Color palettes
often mirror ocean blues, tropical landscapes, and vibrant festival
energy.
</p>

<p>
Design throughout the Caribbean celebrates rhythm, movement, and
storytelling. From architecture to digital art, visual culture
continues to evolve while honoring ancestral creativity.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- FASHION -->

<section id="fashion" class="section container">

<h1>Fashion</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">
<img src="images/fashion.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">
</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Caribbean fashion celebrates self-expression, heritage, and pride.
Designers combine bold prints, natural hair expression, and vibrant
color combinations inspired by island culture.
</p>

<p>
From carnival costumes to everyday streetwear, clothing represents
identity, resilience, and creativity within the global Black diaspora.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- ART -->

<section id="art" class="section container">

<h1>Art</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">
<img src="images/art.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">
</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Visual art across the Caribbean explores themes of memory,
migration, and cultural pride. Artists frequently use symbolism
and storytelling to explore the region's history.
</p>

<p>
Murals, paintings, sculptures, and digital works highlight
community voices while celebrating Black imagination and
innovation.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- ANIMATIONS -->

<section id="animations" class="section container">

<h1>Animations</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">
<img src="images/animation.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">
</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Animation is becoming an important creative space for Caribbean
artists. Through digital storytelling, creators can reimagine
folklore, history, and future visions of Black culture.
</p>

<p>
New animation styles combine 3D modeling, comic aesthetics,
and Caribbean narratives to bring fresh representation to
global media.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- MUSIC -->

<section id="music" class="section container">

<h1>Music</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">
<img src="images/music.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">
</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Music is one of the most influential Caribbean cultural exports.
Genres such as reggae, dancehall, soca, and calypso have shaped
global sound and inspired generations of artists.
</p>

<p>
Beyond entertainment, Caribbean music often reflects political
consciousness, resistance, celebration, and unity.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


<!-- LITERATURE -->

<section id="literature" class="section container">

<h1>Literature</h1>

<div class="row">

<div class="col-md-6">
<img src="images/books.jpg" class="img-fluid zoom">
</div>

<div class="col-md-6">

<p>
Caribbean literature captures powerful narratives about migration,
colonial history, and cultural identity. Writers explore themes
of belonging, heritage, and resistance.
</p>

<p>
Poetry, novels, and oral storytelling traditions remain essential
to preserving Caribbean voices and sharing them with global
audiences.
</p>

</div>

</div>

</section>


